column4: Wells Fargo board faces peculiar problem after lukewarm shareholder vote

column4: Business Watch: Wells Fargo brass gets scorecards
column5: Wells Fargo shareholders showed their dissatisfaction at the banks' board members during an annual meeting that lasted over three hours and was interrupted multiple times due to angry shareholders. Only three directors received more than 90 percent support while  at most S&P 500 companies  director support averages around 95 percent of votes cast.
